SIMPLE: pouched
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pouched
<hw>Pouched</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>Having a marsupial pouch; <as>as, the <ex>pouched</ex>
badger, or the wombat</as>.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>Having external
cheek pouches; <as>as, the <ex>pouched</ex> gopher</as>.</def>
<sd>(c)</sd> <def>Having internal cheek pouches; <as>as, the
<ex>pouched</ex> squirrels</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Pouched dog</b></col>. <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <cd>See
<cref>Zebra wolf</cref>, under <er>Zebra</er>.</cd> -- <col><b>Pouched
frog</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>the nototrema, the female of
which has a dorsal pouch in which the eggs are hatched, and in which the
young pass through their brief tadpole stage.</cd> --
<mcol><col><b>Pouched gopher</b></col>, <it>or</it> <col><b>Pouched
rat</b></col></mcol>. <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <cd>See <cref>Pocket
gopher</cref>, under <er>Pocket</er>.</cd> -- <col><b>Pouched
mouse</b></col>. <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <cd>See <cref>Pocket mouse</cref>,
under <er>Pocket</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pouchet box</ent>⟦br⟧
